text: The California Song-Beverly Consumer Warranty Act provides a 30-day warranty on all new and used
label: BODY

text: hearing aids sold in California.  If the hearing aid is not specifically fit for the buyer's particular needs, the
label: BODY

text: device may be returned to the hearing aid dispenser within 30 days of the date of actual receipt by the
label: BODY

text: buyer or completion of fitting by the seller, whichever occurs later. If the buyer returns the device, the seller
label: BODY

text: must either adjust or replace the device or promptly refund the total amount paid.
label: BODY

text: If the buyer returns the device within the 30-day period, the seller is required, without charge and within a
label: BODY

text: reasonable time, to adjust, repair or replace the device.  If, after the adjustment, repair or replacement, the
label: BODY

text: device is still not specifically fit for the buyer’s particular needs, the device may be returned for a refund of
label: BODY

text: the total amount paid including all payments and any trade-in exchanged as part of the transaction.
label: BODY

text: The Office of the Attorney General’s legal opinion confirms that “the seller may NOT retain any portion of
label: BODY

text: the total amount paid on the basis that such part payment was for fitting the device or other ancillary
label: BODY

text: service or for one or more of the component parts that the seller refuses to take back.” This means the
label: BODY

text: hearing aid dispenser may not retain a fee or other charge in connection with the purchase, fitting,
label: BODY

text: financing, or return of the device, and no fee should be listed as “non-refundable” on the purchase
label: BODY

text: agreement.
label: BODY

text: Application of the Law
label: HH1

text: The hearing aid may be returned at any time within 30 days after the date of the actual delivery or
label: BODY

text: completion of the fitting, whichever occurs later.  For example, if the device is ordered on July 1, and
label: BODY

text: delivered on July 15, it may be returned for adjustment or replacement through August 15.  If, however, the
label: BODY

text: process of the fitting only begins on July 15 and the fitting is not completed until August 20, the buyer is
label: BODY

text: entitled to return the device for adjustment or replacement through September 20.
label: BODY

text: The hearing aid dispenser has the right to attempt to achieve a proper fitting by adjusting, repairing or
label: BODY

text: replacing the device.  If, after the adjustment, the device is still not suited to the buyer’s particular needs,
label: BODY

text: then the device may be returned for a refund of the total amount paid.
label: BODY

text: Buyer’s and Seller’s Responsibilities
label: HH1

text: The hearing aid dispenser must act in good faith in honoring the buyer's rights, and the buyer, too, must act in
label: BODY

text: good faith in enforcing such rights.  Whether the device is or is not specifically fit for the buyer's particular
label: BODY

text: needs will always be a question of fact.  The fact that the buyer sincerely believes that the device is unfit is
label: BODY

text: relevant, but will never be conclusive, just as the fact that the seller believes that the device is fit will never be
label: BODY

text: conclusive.  In a dispute, the opinion of an unrelated third person will be helpful -- but again, never conclusive.
label: BODY

text: As usually is the case, the seller and buyer will have to work to resolve any differences to each other's
label: BODY

text: satisfaction.
label: BODY

text: The buyer does not have an unqualified option to return the device for a refund and may return the hearing aid
label: BODY

text: for a refund only if:
label: BODY

text: (a) the device is not specifically fit for the particular needs of the buyer, and
label: BODY

text: (b) the buyer has not abused the device, and
label: BODY

text: (c) the buyer has returned the device to the seller for adjustment or replacement within the 30 days, and
label: BODY

text: (d) the seller has failed to adjust the device or, if appropriate, replace it with a device that is specifically fit for
label: BODY

text: the buyer's particular needs.
label: BODY

text: The hearing aid dispenser is not required by law to provide a refund if:
label: BODY

text: (a) the device has been abused or damaged by the buyer;
label: BODY

text: (b) the buyer keeps the device for more than 30 days after delivery without seeking an adjustment;
label: BODY

text: (c) the buyer does not allow the dispenser an opportunity to adjust, repair or replace the device;
label: BODY

text: (d) the buyer feels he/she paid too much and returns the hearing aid; or
label: BODY

text: (e) the hearing aid is returned after the death of the buyer.
label: BODY

text: It is important that both the buyer and the seller keep accurate written records of the dates of all adjustments.
label: BODY

text: In a dispute, the records will be essential in making a determination of the issue.
label: BODY

text: The Purchase Agreement Written Warranty Requirement
label: HH2

text: The following warranty language must appear on the hearing aid purchase agreement/receipt delivered to the
label: BODY

text: buyer:
label: BODY

text: This assistive device is warranted to be specifically fit for the particular needs of you, the buyer.  If the
label: BODY

text: device is not specifically fit for your particular needs, it may be returned to the seller within 30 days of
label: BODY

text: the date of actual receipt by you or completion of fitting by the seller, whichever occurs later.  If you
label: BODY

text: return the device, the seller will either adjust or replace the device or promptly refund the total
label: BODY

text: amount paid.  This warranty does not affect the protections and remedies you have under other laws.
label: BODY
